abstract: The former first lady’s long-awaited new memoir recounts with insight, candor and wit her family’s trajectory from the Jim Crow South to Chicago’s South Side and her own improbable journey from there to the White House.
snippet: The former first lady’s long-awaited new memoir recounts with insight, candor and wit her family’s trajectory from the Jim Crow South to Chicago’s South Side and her own improbable journey from there to the White House.
lead_paragraph: BECOMING By Michelle Obama Illustrated. 426 pp. Crown. $32.50.

abstract: Zuleika Hernandez was struggling to pay her bills and keep a full-time job. Then a training program at Hot Bread Kitchen helped her turn things around.
snippet: Zuleika Hernandez was struggling to pay her bills and keep a full-time job. Then a training program at Hot Bread Kitchen helped her turn things around.
lead_paragraph: You can smell the bakery from underneath the East Harlem train tracks long before you see it. Past the retail and takeout stalls of La Marqueta food marketplace, you’ll find Hot Bread Kitchen. As the name suggests, hot bread was coming out of the oven on a recent afternoon.

abstract: A Republican Party that stayed true to President Trump is constrained from grappling with the damage he inflicted with moderate voters and women.
snippet: A Republican Party that stayed true to President Trump is constrained from grappling with the damage he inflicted with moderate voters and women.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — With a brutal finality, the extent of the Republicans’ collapse in the House came into focus last week as more races slipped away from them and their losses neared 40 seats.

abstract: Mr. Bush, a Republican, was a transitional figure in the White House, where he served from 1989 to 1993. He was the last of the World War II generation to occupy the Oval Office.
snippet: Mr. Bush, a Republican, was a transitional figure in the White House, where he served from 1989 to 1993. He was the last of the World War II generation to occupy the Oval Office.
lead_paragraph: George Bush, the 41st president of the United States and the father of the 43rd, who steered the nation through a tumultuous period in world affairs but was denied a second term after support for his presidency collapsed under the weight of an economic downturn and his seeming inattention to domestic affairs, died on Friday night at his home in Houston. He was 94.

abstract: Democrats backed by Mr. Bloomberg’s organization won 21 of 24 House races, making him among the most influential donors of the election cycle.
snippet: Democrats backed by Mr. Bloomberg’s organization won 21 of 24 House races, making him among the most influential donors of the election cycle.
lead_paragraph: A week before the Nov. 6 election, Kendra Horn, a Democratic House candidate in Oklahoma, received unexpected good news from her television consultant: Michael R. Bloomberg’s political action committee, a leading supporter of Democratic candidates, had purchased more than $400,000 in advertising on Oklahoma City television.

abstract: Dozens of possible 2020 Democratic candidates are mulling, weighing, considering, wondering. Here is a guide to how they are communicating a desire to run without announcing it outright.

lead_paragraph: The would-be 2020 Democratic contenders could not be clearer: They are not running for president.
